caption: The food here is very delisious and unique!
Authentic Burmese.   Consistently great service.  Fantastic ambience.    Drinks are solid and consistent.

Only got takeout but the beef curry was tender and flavorful. Potatoes were unsung heroes! Also had stir fried veggies which was soupy but we literally got take out right before closing. Great restaurant in Chinatown.

On a lunch break, we stopped in to grab some food.  No experience with Burmese food, so I figured it would be similar to Nepalese.  Yes and no, distinctive differences, but I was blown away by the Kabet Lamb and Biryani rice.  I overstuffed myself and would have been miserable for it, but it was so incredibly good I don't regret it at all.  This place has been my best dining experience in Hawaii yet.  I highly recommend it if you are a fan of bold and unique flavors.  We will be back here a few more times during out stay here.  Every one of our party of five was raving about how good lunch was.  We are all experienced world travelers, but this is one of my top favorite dining experiences.  The restaurant is clean and have expect staff.  Not pretentious or haughty, just wonderful people bringing a sliver of their culture for us to appreciate.
The food "chef's kiss*. The drinks *chef's kiss*. The playlist 💃. I got the chili chicken and G- force cocktail, highly recommend
Incredible dinner. Restaurant is very nice inside and food is delicious. Full bar. I recommend salads, pumpkin pork curry.
Amazing food. Very great owner! The salsa is perfectly spicy yet very tasty.
Lamb curry and coconut rice. Excellent!
Good
Amazing!! So delicious. We had the Brussels sprouts, fried noodle and coconut curry shrimp with coconut rice. Highly recommend the place
Best food & great service!
Great food. Huge portions.
Great food and nice environment. Even the 9 year old said he would give it a thousand stars!
Mango salad and mushroom and vegetable dish are fire. Love the food and atmosphere here. Great ingredients
Phenomenal food and service. The food was fresh, the service was excellent and it was more than reasonably priced for the portions we received. I cannot reccomend this place enough.

What a delightful surprise. The flavors here are fresh and refreshing as compared to what I'm used to. With the flavors being so pleasing, it was disappointing to find the lamb and squid to be over cooked. Both lamb and squid where tough and very chewy. It was difficult to appreciate the quality of these two as preparation was below average. Otherwise everything else was great. My favorite would have to be the stuffed tofu!
A different taste. The food is made fresh and spice leval can be adjusted to suit your taste buds and tolerance. A wonderful find .
Very healthy and tasty options
Best lamb curry ever! Always delicious and staff is courteous and professional.
Very good food, generous portions. Server made useful suggestions. One dish came out late, but otherwise all good.

Staff was attentive, pleasant and efficient. Clean and attractive restaurant. We had crispy tofu, which was delicious and beautiful presentation. Malaysian Pork curry did not look like any curry that I was familiar with, but was very tasty with a perfect blend of spices. The fried rice also very good. This was our first time at this restaurant and trying out Burmese food was an adventure that we were very pleased with. Will definitely return!
Ordered the Mandaley Meeshay and requested it spicy. They cooked it with chili peppers and the flavors were unbelievable. This was one of the best dishes I've had on the island.

Food was GREAT, service was NOT! Made reservations for dinner on a Saturday night for a party of 11 at 6 pm.  It was very busy with all seats taken, multiple private parties going on and patrons waiting outside to be seated.  However, with a downtown location, I would expect the staff and servers to be used to this kind of busyness. Bad service - Our server was not friendly, seemed irritated when taking our order like we were an inconvenience, 1 main dish and 3 side dishes came when we were done eating.  How can it take THAT long to bring out a bowl a rice and 2 plates of bread?  We had 4 couples in our party so we asked to split the check...it was a MESS.  The alcoholic drinks were split among all the checks, 1 beer was split 4 ways, each check was charged $1.50...huh??!  At first they didn't want to correct it but finally did.  My water was never refilled after asking 2x.  Our original server hardly serviced our table, other servers ended up covering for her. I would go back but request not to have the same server.

(Translated by Google) Lagoon salad seems to be the most popular, so for now. But I want to conquer in order because there are many kinds of salads! Crispy tough, I guess it would be nice to eat it once lol  (Original) ラグーンサラダが1番人気みたいでとりあえず。 けどサラダの種類いっぱいあったから順番に制覇したい！クリスピートウフは、まぁ一回食べたらいい感じかなぁlol
Great food and people. A bit loud when busy, but well worth it!,
Their mango salad is excellent.
Love the Tea Leaf Salad.
Solid!  If you haven't tried Burmese food, the best way to describe it is like a blend if Indian and Southeast Asian cuisine.  Very aromatic.  Wasn't spicy at all, but every flavorful.
Great flavors!
The tea leaf salad here is incredible! We had a large group and they took great care of us. Will definitely pop back in next time we are in Honolulu.

Delicious Tea Leaf Salad, best on the island. The chicken and pork curries have a fish sauce flavor that makes it unlike any other curry, in a good way. The Samusas are great too. Parking is not bad in the evening. You can find free street parking easily in downtown, or use one of the many paid lots.
Loved the ambience, service and great food
Excellent food but service and cleanliness needs improvement.
Very good food.  Crowded at lunch.
Very good food. Great atmosphere. Friendly service.
This is a very unique Restaurant.  The food IS REALLY GOOD.  The taste is like a blend of different Asian cuisines. Hard to put into words,  put your tastebuds & stomach will love it.

(Translated by Google) Quite standard Burmese food, vegetable curry flavor is quite prominent, coconut milk flavor does not cover other vegetable flavors. Overall sweet, but still quite adequate.  (Original) 相當有水準的緬甸菜，蔬菜咖哩味道相當突出，椰奶味沒有蓋過其他蔬菜味道。整體偏甜，但仍然相當夠水準。
Food is great as always. They need to perform maintenance to address HVAC and lighting issues.

Hyped up and overrated. Went at 6pm on a Saturday and asked for a table for 2 and they said they were booked the whole night and could not seat us even at the bar even tho we said we could wait.  If you want Burmese food, go to their sister restaurant Dagon. Same menu, cheaper prices, friendlier staff and BYOB.  Rangoon is located in a spot where all previous restaurants have failed and with an attitude like the hostess gave us, I guarantee they’re going to fail too.

(Translated by Google) Hidden stores in downtown Delicious Burmese cuisine is a specialty ^ _ ^ Everything was delicious, especially the garlic noodles!  (Original) ダウンタウンの隠れた名店 美味しいビルマ料理が名物です^_^ どれも美味しかったですが、特にガーリックヌードルは最高でした！
Delicious.
Fun spot,not sure how j feel about the curry there, in general pretty decent.
Food was awesome! Ti leaf salad, stuffed tofu, creamy coconut curry beef and fish curry...all delish! Will go back...

I got the Burmese curry with lamb. It was so flavorful and delicious! It was also a ton of food - I hadn't eaten until I went here for lunch, and I still couldn't finish all the food. I got a side of rice, and also some of these flaky bread things to eat with the curry - I would recommend one or the other. (Note that both are an extra charge - the curry doesn't come with rice.)
My first delicious food in Honolulu. This was my first time eating Burmese cuisine and the curry chicken dish was absolutely delicious. The appetizer platha and curry dip also was fantastic.
Fabulous food, fresh and delicious! Our server was very helpful with suggestions as we had never had Burmese food before. Nice cocktail menu too. Warm, cozy atmosphere.
Way better than Waikiki! Incredible food albeit bit slow due to staff shortage.
Great food.  Great drinks. And service!
Excellent food and service!
Really tasty food! Kind of a hybrid between Thai and Indian.
BYOB and, Fantastic food! A must ! Check em out

Wow! What an experience. The food is so delish! You can't go wrong with anything on the menu. I keep going back. The Biryani is such a beautiful and fragrant dish. Scents of cinnamon, lemon grass, & cumin... ahh Have it with the lamb. Oh I can smell it now as I write. The Ti leaf salad it's full of texture and flavors that will surely keep your tastebuds busy. We've had the veggie coconut curry, veggie noodles and the Fried tofu salad. On their cocktail list start with the first one called Passion something ... and work your way down. Do yourself a flavor and go to Rangoon Burmese!
Outstanding food and drinks.
Interesting food
Meet my perspective paste
Very bad experience! Food was not as I expected,service was equally bad. Also there were cockroach on my table! Yes !! Disgusting!
Awesome people and service.

It's the closest thing my wife and I can find similar to Indonesian food on Oahu.  The coconut rice was great, we also had the spicy lamb, pork stew with pumpkin and the basil chicken.  all very good.
Delicious!! I don't think I've had anything I didn't like. Would recommend to everyone!!
Food is excellent, its very similar to Indian style cooking. Enjoyed lot.
Food are very good.  Services are good.  Big portions.   We ordered Tea salad, beef curry and chile chicken.  All of them are very good.
Amazing choices! Beautiful decor, nice clean restroom.

Dined here on a Saturday night. S-L-O-W-E-S-T service in the whole wide world. We sat at one of the high tables but had to move because the table was so wobbly, it was impossible to eat. We moved to the bar hoping service might be faster, but wrong. The bartender was so S-L-O-W, an amateur. He looked so stressed, wiping sweat from his face and head. I ordered a martini and my partner ordered a beer. The slow bartender commented "if only everyone orders this (beer)..." as he placed the tap glass on the counter. What a mess. We waited, and waited, and waited.  I thought it was the other way around, that you, the WAITer and WAITress should WAIT on us? Otherwise, I could have stayed home. We had to wait for the bartender to take our orders, each time. Did not follow-up on whether our food was okay, did not follow-up on our drinks if we want anymore, water glass sitting empty for a while, and no question on whether we needed anything else. We had to flag him each time, for another tap of beer, for some napkins, for anything else. The woman who gave us our first dish said "sorry about the wait". We asked her for hot sauce, she said the hot sauce is right there pointing at a red sauce included with our noodle dish. No, we had to clarify for the hot peppers in a jar. Why waste our time to make your sarcastic point - duh there is a hot sauce there - but you knew we were asking for a condiment hot sauce, not the noodle sauce that actually came with the dish. The same woman later came to the bar to look at the order monitor in front of us, then we asked a waiter and the bartender for our check. They kept us waiting. Mind you, we were at the bar right in front of the bartender. He can directly observe us, whether we were done with a dish, needed a water refill or napkins, or wanted to order some more from the menu. I suggest for any staff here to be more observant of their customers, who pay them to keep this business running. How can we be in front of you and you still did not know what we need? I complained that we have been waiting, and the stupid woman, who kept saying the same thing for at least the past two hours, again said 'sorry about the wait'. ENOUGH F--- SORRY IF YOU ARE NOT GOING TO FIX IT. We did more waiting on the wait staff than actual eating. We took our food home because we were ignored, and it was one of the worst dining experiences I have ever had. I will not return to this restaurant. I will be in Yangon next month to have the real deal. The bartender did not even say thank you when we left. The woman also did not do anything else. Inferior customer service as compared to any restaurant in downtown. We have dined at almost every restaurant in downtown where the service had always been exquisite. With so many other downtown restaurants competing for your business, the Rangoon Burmese Kitchen is the worst in the area. What's up? Your poor service might be acceptable at restaurants in Yangon, but hello, this is NOT Yangon. Both the Caucasian bartender and waiter and both the Asian waitress and waiter seem to especially favor certain customers by a race which, really is not a biggie to me until you treat me with the poorest customer service, then it becomes personal. Good luck with that mentality in Hawaii where diversity is prevalent. Lastly, the dining room was very loud. It was just so nice and peaceful to walk out of there and turn my back away from the mediocrity. Shame on you for making us pay for your bad service and ruining a date night.

Love the food, but service is HORRIBLE at lunch.  They are pretty nice, but so inefficient. If you don't call right when they open, they rarely answer the phone since the ringer is barely audible and they are understaffed but have no sense of urgency.  The hot food is always bagged with the cold salads, and I've only received utensils one time.  Eating in not as bad since I'm not usually as pressed for time, but I wouldn't go there if I was.
Every dish was incredible!
The rangoon tea leaf salad surprise me!

Surprising spices, hearty, generous portions. Family style eating rewarded. Great and attentive servers (who could be a bit better versed in the nuances of Burmese fare). Extra points for the perfect, spicy, oily hot mess that is the Burmese lamb curry. Perfectly soft and friendly, unctuous and complex. Will be back!!
So good! Must try the Rangoon Tea Leaf Salad!

The food was good but the service was terrible. They said they just got slammed with a big group, however we were basically ignored the entire time with exception of the bartender, he apologized multiple times, but it never got better even though we were basically the only ones there. It was close to closing time, but they also forgot to put in my wife's food. It might be better during the middle of the evening or they had an off night. The food was really good though.

Wish I could have given 5 stars but the food was over salted, the rice was undercooked, and the restaurant was understaffed. There was only 1 server for the whole place so the bartender had to pitch in. The food was tasty and unique, just salty. The tea leaf salad was refreshing and the coconut curry was very rich and creamy. They were recommended to us by the waiter and were a nice pair.
Thai influences and maybe Chinese.definitely a different experience.

(Translated by Google) I ate chicken curry. Exceptionally soft and holo! It was delicious for Asian food enthusiasts. I regretted that I could only eat one dish because I went alone while waiting for the Japanese consulate. It is recommended to go by 3-4 people because of the large amount.  (Original) チキンカレーを食べました。　ホロホロに柔らかく絶品！アジアンフード好きにはたまらない美味しさでした。 日本領事館へ行った際の待ち時間に一人で行ったので、一品しか食べられなかったのが悔しい。　量も多いので3～4人で行くのをお勧めします。
I was greatly disappointed that it was not true Burmese dishes. There was nothing wrong with the food or service.  Unfortunately I can not give this place more than three stars.

I had heard nothing but rave reviews of this place and I think my expectations were already set high; so when my meal was a little lackluster, I just left feeling just meh about this place.  Do not get me wrong, this restaurant has some amazing dishes but the ones that were raved about by my friends were just meh to me.  Next time I am going to try some dishes that I was eyeing in the first place but didnt end up ordering tonight.

We've been here a couple of times, very good. We had the Rangoon Tea Leaf Salad, Mashed Potato Salad and the Garlic Noodle with tofu. The atmosphere is very chill and the staff is kind and knowledgeable. We will definitely be going back again.... and again. See you there! Aloha
Outstanding! Everything we tried was awesome - beef kebat, mint chicken, and the tea leaf salad. Try it all because it’s amazing
Excellent restaurant!
Food was AWESOME. Everything delicious. They just need to step up the service and cleanliness (bathroom) a bit. Seems like they might be a little understaffed... victim of their own success?
Excellent food and ambiance
The food is delish and the staff is helpful and friendly
Charming, tasty, interesting. My new favorite spot in Honolulu's Chinatown. Don't miss the tealeaf salad or the curries.
Food is awesome prices are just as great. Sometimes it can take a bit to be noticed and seated. Majority of the waiter/waitresses are helpful and can point you in the right direction.
Excellent food, great service! Very unique restaurant and cuisine.

Each and every dish has something amazingly unique about it in addition to being perfectly cooked & seasoned. I regularly dine all over Honolulu and I have not been as impressed as I was during my visit to Rangoon in a long time. Must try restaurant, must go back to try each item on the menu. Bring a group of at least four so you can try many dishes, you won't be disappointed. I wish I could give this establishment more stars for the menu. While service was a bit slow, we arrived with only 1 hour remaining to lunch. Establishment is in the process of servicing liquor items, with food like this you won't miss the alcohol.
The flavors were on point! Loved all the fresh herbs and spices. Rainbow salad was amazing, as well as the Samusas!  BYOB at the moment, will be serving alcohol soon.
(Translated by Google) Tea leaf salad Chicken Biryani Katchinfish  (Original) ティーリーフサラダ チキンのビリヤニ カチンフィッシュ
Amazingly Delicious Dishes (VEGAN)

The food is quite delicious. The flavors are layered and subtle. The Tea Leaf Salad offers rich textures. The Brussel Sprouts with Dried Fish appetizer was probably my favorite choice that day, although the Burmese Fish Curry was also a standout. What most impressed our party was the fact that we arrived 20 minutes before the 2:00 closing of lunch hours, yet the service was excellent and we were not rushed by the staff. Atmosphere is vogue and comfortable, welcoming to professionals on lunch break, families, locals and visitors alike.
Great food, byob
(Translated by Google) delicious! ! You do not need to reserve lunch! !  (Original) 美味しい！！ランチは予約しなくても大丈夫！！
I went with friends, the Rangoon salad was my favorite,  we had salad stuffed fried tofu. Basil chicken, and Burmese rice.  Reservations are probably preferred,  as was quite busy!
Visited the place twice and as expected it was very tasty. I recommend this place for those who like mild curry and tasty Asian food.

This place was very good esp since I have a sensitive to spice palate. We got the pumpkin stew curry with chicken -- soo good!! And then the pineapple shrimp fried rice yummmm. Its BYOB since they're still waiting on their liquor license.

Very tasty, seems like a fusion of Asian/southeast asian cusines.  Very similar to Thai curry and basil.  I especially liked the pineapple fried rice and pork belly.  Friendly staff, inviting decor, great family style asian restaurant, also BYOB!
The food here is so good. I keep thinking about when I can go back again...

I honestly had no idea what to expect from this place. I had never been there or even heard of it. From the moment you walk into the doors the atmosphere gets you. It is well decorated, authentic and fun. I recommend making reservations as it was very busy and when the food was served I knew why. We started with the Rangoon Tea leaf salad and had the mango shrimp stir fry and the coconut lamb curry for entrees. It was absolutely delicious!

This was my second visit...the food is great and the portions too large unless you have hungry diners... my issues are: the food comes out slowly and there isn't enough wait staff to ensure prompt and attentive service. Thus, it's a mixed review...great food, slow service ... 1.5hr lunch is a little long for most patrons
Very good Burmese
Wow. Ordered 7 dishes and every single one was over the top fabulous. Normally I don't do 5 star... This deserves it.

Definitely a must go to and must return to restaurant.  Great food, friendly staff and BYOB make it an inexpensive night of good food. You have to start off with the samusa. A great appetizer to start and perfect for two couples (4 pieces) or a couple with a very hungry person.  We also had the lemongrass prawns which was cooked to perfection. The girls weren't impressed by the "head on" presentation but that just meant extra for me.  The brussel sprouts are also a must have dish but avoid the Thai Peppers unless you can handle the heat.  The Rangoon Tea Leaf salad was just an okay dish to me - nothing special.  My highlight of this dinner was the Kachin Whole Fish Wrapped in Banana Leaf. Whole Moi and Warabi shoots wrapped and baked in Banana Leaf that just melted in your mouth. Definitely will order this again.  Always a great meal with great food at reasonable cost.
Wow! The ginger salad is a must! Great staff, amazing food.
It was Excellent and the food was Outstanding
Such amazing food! And service was the best! Ginger Salad, not what you expect, but so good!

Amazingly good food. Burmese cuisine is very unique and very good, and this restaurant is a great place  to try it. The tea leaf salad a very unique dish, and really tasty-I highly recommend it as a starter! The portions are small, so be sure to order a couple items if you're hungry!
Flavorful Burmese dishes with elegant interior decor. Highly recommend the Kachin Whole Fish Wrapped in Banana Leaf and the Green Tea Salad.

Our favorite was the platha bread and the coconut rice. I got the shan noodles, which were very flavorful and delicious but the noodles felt overcooked as they were mushy. I like a my noodles al dente so maybe this is subjective. The service was okay, a little slow because they were understaffed for a Saturday. I felt my server was inattentive and was busy looking over the next table... but this restaurant just opened so I’m sure they will get the kinks fixed.
(Translated by Google) A sister store of Dagon of kaimuki. Everything was delicious ~ ♪ Salad is quite famous.  (Original) カイムキのダゴンの姉妹店。全部美味しかった～♪サラダが結構有名かも。

This is a new hotspot in Chinatown serving up authentic Burmese cuisine. All of the dishes are so fresh.  A must-try is the tea leaf salad which is a very popular Burmese dish. It consists of fermented green tea leaf mixed with romaine lettuce, garlic chips, beans, peanuts, yellow split pea, green split pea, sesame seed, sunflower seed, tomato, jalapeño and lime. Very light and refreshing!  They are still working on their liquor license so it’s B.Y.O.B. for now. The staff is knowledgeable about the menu items and very friendly.  Be sure to tell your server about any dietary preferences! They can easily make modifications for vegans.
Never had Burmese food before and it was amazing
Love the dishes
(Translated by Google) Strong spices unique to Southeast Asia. It's a traditional Burma food, but it does not seem to be Korean.  (Original) 동남아 특유의 향신료 강함. 전통 버마 음식인데 한국인 입맛엔 아닌듯 ㅠㅠ
Great food, Experience something new and enjoy it, you will come back.

Unique cuisine, huge portions, friendly service. First time for Burmese food, but have much experience with Indian and Thai.  This was like the best of both.  Complex, exotic, not spicy hot.  The dishes were all sharing size, very large. Ginger salad was very unique. Take a pic before it’s mixed at your table.  Mo hin ga stew was amazing. Burmese lamb curry was my favorite.  Delightful service and menu suggestions by Mai. I would definitely return.
Excellent dishes...flavorful food that wakes up thw taste buds...customer service is getting better the more i go
Service was a bit slow. But it wasn't really busy. Food was excellent.
Excellent Burmese food!
The food was really tasty and rich in flavor. Friendly staff, huge portions and very reasonable prices
Very cozy place & love this area...Super Delicious guys! U have to try this!!

Been twice in a week, once for dinner, once for lunch. Same menu, different dishes each time. Subtle compared to Indian or Thai but great/unexpected mixes of ingredients, flavors, and textures. Will return soon, so much more to explore.

Huge selection of food.  I went for lunch and everything we ordered was tasty.  The tea leaf salad was my favorite. Price was pretty much what we expected, but not so high that I wouldn't go back, cuz I'll definitely be returning to try some of the other dishes.  Service was a little off, but super nice staff, could have been that we got there at the end of the lunch shift.

Really amazing food and flavors.  Nice and comfortable restaurant.  Service was a bit slow, but they were clearly understaffed for the time we dined at, but the food made up for it.  Will recommend and return for sure. The Rangoon Tea Leaf Salad, Chili Chicken, and Eggplant Curry were amazing.
One of the newer restaurants to open in Chinatown. Delicious cuisine packed full of flavor. If you like Burmese food, this place will hit the spot.
The food was so delicious and well seasoned. Great customer service I will return again.

Every dish will have you salivating and craving more. Phenomenal menu items. Best if you go with friends and share dishes 'family style'. Platha bread, Tea leaf salad and coconut curry lamb were my favorite items. Service was exceptional with our large party. Will for sure be going back soon.

Went to china town for , well.. Chinese food. However we were persuaded otherwise when we passed this cool looking Burmese restaurant. The results were mixed but this place has great potential The samosas were crisp and flavoursome and came with a delicious sour dipping sauce Likewise the Burmese slow cooked curries, we had both pork and beef, were delicious. The meat meltingly soft and the sauce deep with flavour. Unfortunately the other half of the meal was bland at best. The chicken Shan noodles dish lacked any defining flavours or real texture. Likewise the whole baked fish was the worst Asian steamed fish I’ve tasted - both mushy and tasteless

One of the best new restaurants to try in Honolulu! Go with a large group of friends so you can order family style and try as many things as possible! They have a couple of sections that are set aside for groups of 8-10; the best is the one next to the street with the windows.  My suggestions: Mashed Potato Salad, Sour Tea Leaf Salad, and Coconut Curry Lamb. It’s BYOB, so I brought a Prosecco that paired very well with all of it!
